SIMPLE: podophyllum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Podophyllum
<hw>Pod`o*phyl"lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>poy`s</grk>, <grk>podo`s</grk>, foot + <grk>fy`llon</grk>
leaf.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of herbs of the
Barberry family, having large palmately lobed peltate leaves and
solitary flower. There are two species, the American <spn>Podophyllum
peltatum</spn>, or May apple, the Himalayan <spn>Podophyllum
Emodi</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The rhizome and rootlet of the May
apple (<spn>Podophyllum peltatum</spn>), -- used as a cathartic
drug.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Podoscaph</ent>⟦br⟧
